The paper deals with improving the PAC-Bayesian error bound for linear regression, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the application of the error bound to time series generated by certain classes of dynamical models, which falls under the sub-category of statistics (cs.ST) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of non-independent training data, which is relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
